														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4601417">
									

<p>I didn't like it at all.</p>
<p>I see some potential, but there's a huge problem regarding the fact that it makes SUCH a HUGE deal of it.<br />
It constantly builds up and builds up but then it just ends and gives nothing, it's not bad, it's disappointing. You expect this SCP to have a really cool and deep&#8230; something&#8230; but it just gives you [DATA EXPUNGED] and [REDACTED] the entire time, it would make me think, if there was something to think about.</p>
<p>Get 001 as an example, the fact that no info in it is granted for sure and as far as we know they can all be real or can all be fake, makes it so mysterious and puts you to think(besides what each proposition gives alone). 579 just makes a big deal out of nothing, basically.</p>
<p>In conclusion:<br />
If it didn't made such a huge deal out of it or simply gave anything for us to think about, it would be great.</p>

